alert.note: Alert for Gadsden; Leon; Liberty; Wakulla (Florida) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued January 25 at 8:46AM EST until January 25 at 10:00AM EST by NWS Tallahassee
info.description: The National Weather Service in Tallahassee has issued a * Severe Thunderstorm Warning for... Northwestern Wakulla County in Big Bend of Florida... Gadsden County in Big Bend of Florida... Central Liberty County in Big Bend of Florida... Leon County in Big Bend of Florida... Decatur County in southwestern Georgia... Grady County in southwestern Georgia... Northwestern Thomas County in south central Georgia... * Until 1000 AM EST. * At 845 AM EST, severe thunderstorms were located along a line extending from 9 miles north of West Bainbridge to 10 miles east of Stonemill Creek, moving east at 20 mph. HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts. SOURCE...Radar indicated. IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees. * Locations impacted include... Quincy, Tallahassee, Havana, Bainbridge, Midway, Cairo, Ochlocknee, Whigham, Florida State University, Tallahassee Comm College, Doak Campbell Stadium, Greensboro, Florida A And M, West Bainbridge, Gretna, Attapulgus, Climax, Lake Bradford, Jewel Fire Tower and Capel. TORNADO...POSSIBLE HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED MAX HAIL SIZE...<.75 IN WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH
info.instruction: A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1100 AM EST for Big Bend of Florida. For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a building. A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1100 AM EST for Big Bend of Florida.
